THE discovery of a rotting body in a hospital ceiling has left medical staff shocked and confused. The unidentified body was found at Mahatma Gandhi Memorial Hospital in Phoenix, north of Durban by security guards. This was after they were alerted by hospital employees. “It all started with a smell at the beginning of the week. But they ignored it,” said the source. “When the smell got worse on Friday, they tried to find out where it came from. That’s when they stumbled on the body.” KZN health spokeswoman Ncumisa Mafunda said the department was shocked and concerned. Police spokesman Lieutenant- Colonel Thulani Zwane confirmed the discovery. He said an inquest docket was opened.